gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Clippers 131, Kings 117
gameRecap.excerpt: The Clippers defeated the Kings, 131-117. Kawhi Leonard recorded a team-high 34 points, along with nine rebounds and three assists for the Clippers, while James Harden added 26 points, six assists and five steals in the victory. DeAaron Fox led all scorers with 40 points, along with five rebounds and three assists for the Kings in the losing effort. The Clippers improve to 8-9 on the season, while the Kings fall to 10-7.
